Vice President Mike Pence met with President Nicos Anastasiades of the Republic of Cyprus at the White House. Pence expressed U.S. support for the resumption of UN-facilitated talks in Geneva and hopes for a settlement that would reunify Cyprus as a bizonal, bicommunal federation. They discussed the strong partnership between the United States and Cyprus, as well as areas for further cooperation. Pence also thanked Cyprus for its contributions to the Global Coalition to Counter ISIS and its commitment to support the Middle East peace process.